%[text] 2\. 
%[text] The simulated results differ from theory by 6%, 10% and 4% respectively. The theoretical value lies within the simulations confidence interval for the first two so the discrepancy  is consistent with sampling error but the last stat is not within the confidence interval so the discrepancy sugests a bias.
%[text] 
